{"sections":[],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You cannot adjust for your bias because it is a fundamental part of how you understand the world. It is at a lower level than your senses and changes what you see, smell, and feel."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"While you can’t adjust for your bias, you can alter it over time by exposing yourself to other points of view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"date: 2016-05-14T10:45:40-05:00","type":"text"}],"topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/05-14-adjusting-for-your-bias","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/05-14-adjusting-for-your-bias"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016"]]},"metadata":{"title":"Adjusting For Your Bias","modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"},"platforms":[{"name":"Brunow","introducedAt":"2017.01.20"}]},"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/brunow","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he."}],"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","title":"Brunow"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/Archive":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"All posts"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"Archive","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/ar